{
  "_comment": [
    "Moonshine moonshine-tiny per-tensor tolerances for compare_tensors.py.",
    "",
    "Provisional - magnitude-aware budget derived from per-tensor sidecar",
    "statistics (p99_abs and rms recorded by scripts/lib/ref_dump.py::",
    "write_tensor). Recipe:",
    "  max_abs  = max(1e-4 * p99_abs, 1e-6)   # 0.01% of typical large value",
    "  mean_abs = max(1e-5 * rms,     1e-6)   # 0.001% of RMS energy",
    "Rationale: observed fp32-vs-fp32 drift between two correct",
    "implementations (different BLAS, different reduction order, FMA vs",
    "mul+add) is typically ~1e-5 relative; this prior is 10x looser to",
    "admit benign cross-library variation but tight enough that a real",
    "port issue (wrong layer norm epsilon, missing residual, wrong scale)",
    "trips the budget on first Stage 4 run. The 1e-6 floor catches near-",
    "zero tensors where the relative budget would otherwise vanish.",
    "",
    "Stage 4 (porting-4-cpp) finalizes these against observed C++ drift,",
    "replaces _provisional with permanent values, and removes this",
    "comment block. Do NOT ship a model while _provisional entries remain."
  ],
